-- TABLE-Euro zone M3 growth up in June, private loans contract
-- 
-- Fri Jul 25, 2014 04:37AM EDT
-- None



FRANKFURT, July 25 (Reuters) - Lending to households and firms in the euro zone contracted further in June, while money supply growth picked up, the European Central Bank said on Friday.

The ECB gave the following percentage changes in growth,  seasonally adjusted:JUNEMAY   Prior   M3 annual growth rate   1.51.0   (1.0)  M3 3-month moving avg 12-mo growth  1.10.9   (0.9)   Annual total credit growth -2.3   -2.3  (-2.3)   Annual credit growth private sector-2.2   -2.6  (-2.5)-- of which loans -1.7   -2.0  (-2.0)   -- of which loans (adj. for sales   and securitisation)   -1.1   -1.4  (-1.4)  Breakdown of Loans, pct annual growth rate:   Loans to households-0.6   -0.7  (-0.7)-- consumer credit-1.5   -2.2  (-2.2)-- for home purchases -0.4   -0.3  (-0.3)   Loans to non-financial corporations-2.3   -2.6  (-2.6)  Loans to NFCs adj. for sales and   securitisation -2.3   -2.5  (-2.5)  Monthly loan flow to firms (bln euros)   -2 -9(-8)